2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: "The Siege Of Paris" continues as foot soldier Mads documents the brutality of the siege and winter threatens to do what the trebuchets can't quite manage: wipe out his army. One late night commando-style raid across the frigid Seine to the very walls of Paris suggests a possible way out and a victory that a few hundred have denied tens of thousands.
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: The Siege of Paris, Part 2

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: The awesome underwater issue! Guest-starring Aqualad, Arthur Jr., Inky, Fluffy and Steve, the Sea Horse! Aquagirl introduces everybody to her new Tiny Titans team, "The Hurtin' Titans!" Featuring: Hardrock, The Face, Star Spangled Kid and TNTeena! Ker-sploosh!

In a perfect world, what could possibly go wrong? An exciting new story by Eisner Award Winning writers JOHN LAYMAN (Chew) and LEE GARBETT (Batgirl). Peter Parker thinks life couldn’t get any better—until an explosion at Horizon Labs plummets him (along with Deadpool and Hulk) into another dimension where The Amazing - Spider is the world’s most powerful and beloved hero and Peter Parker is a billionaire mogul playboy (with surprises in his supporting cast). Will Peter discover the price for perfection? And what dreams come true does this dimension hold for Deadpool and Hulk? Find out as the story continues in their respective Annuals in May and June.
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: Identity Wars, Part 1 of 3

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: For the last year, tensions have been building between the two Outsiders teams – now it's all-out war! It's Outsider vs. Outsider as Geo-Force is finally pushed to the edge when he learns Black Lightning and his team have invaded Markovia in an attempt to overthrow Geo-Force's rule. It's a battle royal that not even Batman may be able to stop!
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: Beginning of the End

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: “MEANWHILE” Cyclops, Emma, Wolverine and Armor are off in Japan dealing with giant monsters. Meanwhile, something dire happens that demands the attention of the X-Men. With their leaders away, should the X-Men deny their help? HELL NO! Storm, Colossus and Kitty Pryde join Beast and Agent Brand to take on the Brood. But when intergalactic law prevents the destruction of an enemy who can only be defeated by extermination, the X-Men have a problem. Are Storm and her crew up to the task? And what is Cyclops going to say when he learns of this? This adventure takes place at the same time as the MONSTROUS arc concurrently happening in Astonishing X-Men in a way never before seen!
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: Meanwhile, Part One

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: Byzantium Mack's granddaughter, Lotus Blossom, is a violent and cunning would-be conjuror. Now, she's taken over the House of Mystery and turned it into something…strange. But not everyone is taking this lying down. And why is Harry sleeping with – well, we can't say who.
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: Lost Advantages: Desolation, Part 3 of 5; Communion

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: Uh-oh…looks like Deadpool made a slight miscalculation. Sure, he wants to die—but he doesn’t want to take down thousands of innocent people with him! It was almost impossible for Deadpool to convince Hulk to come after him—how the hell is he supposed to convince him to stop?
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: Operation: Annihilation Part Two: Clear and Present Anger

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: While Red Hulk is flying cross country due to the possessed Thing's powerhouse assault, his foes M.O.D.O.K and Zero/One team up to combat the Invading Nazi hordes (they can't let somebody ELSE sieze control, after all).
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: Planet of Fear, Pt. 2

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: Deathstroke battles Arsenal for the leadership of the Titans in the finale of "The Methusalah Imperative." But as two bitter foes face off, Osiris and Dr. Sivana make a pact that will change the Marvel Family forever. Meanwhile, one mystery remains – who will wield the catastrophic power of the Methuselah device? Guest-starring Jericho!
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: The Methuselah Imperative, Part 3 of 3

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description: Chrono's crusade to recover the remaining piece of the music program runs into a demonic obstacle-Velsper. And speaking of demons, when Hild drops in by surprise on Keiichi's birthday, it's not to give best wishes . . . it's because there's been a coup in hell!
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: Volume 38

2011-01-01|2011-12-30.description:
Who Was Ben Reilly? Concludes! Peter Parker’s past collides with his future! Can Peter Parker save his family and himself?!!

Plus, Deadpool-Man, Deadpool-Man – does whatever a Deadpool can…spins a web any size – but not really…Deadpool’s don’t have webs. Look out! Here comes the Deadpool-Man! What force on Earth could possibly induce Webheaded Wonder and the Merc with a Mouth to team-up?!! More importantly, will Spidey’s sanity survive the encounter?!

Also, classic adventure as Spider-Man finds himself caught between Blacklash, the Scorpion and the Rhino!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #610-611 and Amazing Spider-Man #319.
Translates Shadowland: Blood on the Streets #1-4, Shadowland: Moon Knight #1-3 and Shadowland: Power Man #1-4.
2011-01-01|2011-12-30.name: Shadowland
